      "title": "FLORENCE Batch Image",
      "properties": {
        "ue_properties": {
          "widget_ue_connectable": {},
          "version": "7.7",
          "input_ue_unconnectable": {}
        }
      },
      "widgets_values": [
        "This image from batch node is used to contextualize action from a particular frame. For instance if I have a video where two characters high five halfway through, and the video is 100 frames total, I would set the batch index to frame 50 as THAT is when they high five.\n\nThe batch index determines which frame the action defining action image will come from.  \n\nDo NOT adjust the length, as more than 1 image will cause Florence to output multiple prompts."
      ],
      "color": "#332922",
      "bgcolor": "#593930"
    },
